# this has to be the first entry
PortSystem           1.0

# a one-sentence description of the port
description          BPEL2oWFN translates BPEL processes into Petri nets.

# a long description (break long lines with escaped newlines)
long_description     BPEL2oWFN is a tool translating business processes \
                     described in BPEL to open workflow nets (oWFN). This \
                     oWFN can be used to (1) check for controllability or \
                     generate the operating guideline using the tool Fiona \
                     or Wendy, (2) check for deadlocks or any other Petri \
                     net property using the tool LoLA, or (3) check any \
                     temporal logic formula with a variety of model \
                     checking tools. Furthermore, BPEL2oWFN can translate \
                     a BPEL4Chor choreography to a Petri net model. This \
                     model can be used to analyze properties of a complete \
                     choreography or to synthesize a fitting service for \
                     an incomplete choreography. BPEL2oWFN uses static \
                     analysis to make the generated Petri net model as \
                     compact as possible to analyze a chosen property. \
                     This is called flexible model generation. Furthermore, \
                     several design flaws can be detected using control and \
                     data flow analysis.


